replies.bodyText:
Yes, but the thing is, sourceOS is a variable that holds the name of the target OS and has not yet anything to do with src/.... It's only used for determining the rootPath, which should actually be path_to_target_OS_sources:
String targetOs = projectConfiguration.getTargetTriplet().getOs();
Path targetSourcePath = paths.getSourcePath().resolve(targetOs);

